  <steps>
    <step num="0">Preheat oven to 400˚F (200˚C). </step>
    <step num="1">Peel and cut onions into ½-inch (1 cm) rings. Separate the rings. </step>
    <step num="2">Wrap a piece of bacon around one onion ring. Repeat with remaining onion rings and place on a parchment paper-lined baking sheet. </step>
    <step num="3">Combine the BBQ sauce and honey in a bowl, and brush onto rings. </step>
    <step num="4">Bake for 20 minutes, or until golden brown. </step>
    <step num="5">Enjoy! </step>
  </steps>
